<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Rohan Unleashed Part 1<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.67)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4825'>Sean "RogueHound" Campbell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4825&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> October 16, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> ROHAN CULTURE <br>
<br>
What better way to kick off an Article on Rohan but in Alphabetical order. We start with Eomer and his 3 Cards (So Far). We find the usually fun stats that all Men who arent named Aragorn have. You might say, No big whoop!  Ill throw him in my box with Hobbit-pump Boromir Dont count him out just yet. <br>
<br>
<br>
Eomer, Sister-Son of Theoden (3) <br>
Companion - Man <br>
7/3/A<br>
While you can spot a [Rohan] Man, Eomer&#39;s twilight cost is -1.  At the start of each turn, you may heal a [Rohan] Ally.<br>
Now indeed there is hope of victory.<br>
4 C 266<br>
<br>
The common Eomer will be able to start with Eowyn and Theoden to make a great Rohan start combine that with his ability to Heal a Rohan Ally who will in turn heal you back, liberate a site (with Theodens Game text) and provide strength Bonuses. <br>
<br>
 Eomer, Third Marshal of Riddermark (3) <br>
Companion - Man <br>
7/3/T <br>
While you can spot a [Rohan] Man, Eomer&#39;s twilight cost is -1. Eomer <br>
is strength +2 for each wound on each minion he is skirmishing. <br>
&#39;Then one rode forward, a tall man, taller than the rest; from his <br>
helm as a crest a white horsetail flowed.&#39; <br>
4 R 267 <br>
<br>
As all Companions in the first 3 sets Eomer comes in Rare form too!  This Version of Eomer is a beast. Put him on his horse with spear and he is a power 11 (if the minion assigned was not exhausted to start) Damage +2  super machine. Each wound makes him more and more vicious against each opponent. Great Combo in open tournaments without any more cards being spoiled would be <br>
<br>
A Rangers Versatility with Aragorn out against a Witch King/Cave Troll<br>
Send up Eomer with spear and he is a power 15 add a Flaming Brand and he bumps up to 16 against Troll and 18 against The King.  <br>
I see the Rare Eomer becoming awesome in any kind of Archery Deck. Each time you see them pluck a wound down on a minion you can watch Eomer get bigger and bigger.<br>
<br>
Eomers Spear (1) <br>
Possession - Hand Weapon <br>
Str +2 <br>
Bearer Must be a [Rohan] Man. If Bearer is Eomer and he is Mounted he is Damage +2 <br>
 He advanced until the point of his spear was within a foot of Aragorns Breast&#39; <br>
4 U 268<br>
<br>
Awesome card deploys for 1, gives a +2 Bonus and unlike most Unique () weapons this one can deploy to any Rohan Man Oh no I got Eomers Spear but no Eomer!! Drop it on anyone else.  No damage bonus though but you can always transfers possessions during the Fellowship Phase. <br>
<br>
<br>
Eowyn, Lady of Rohan (2) <br>
Companion - Man <br>
6/3/T <br>
Valiant <br>
Response: If an unbound companion is about to take a wound, exert Eowyn and add (1) to prevent that wound. <br>
4 C 270 <br>
<br>
This card has been out for a while and I swear I almost want to but $9.99 worth or Decipher products since I have too many of these cards and dont want another.  We have Eowyn in Common form and she is like a Built in Shoulder to Shoulder for any Unbound Companion. This can be used to prevent Gandalf from dying due to Too Great And Terrible. Even preventing a companion from dying due to Uruk-Hai Damage +1.  <br>
<br>
Eowyn,  Sister-Daughter of Theoden (2) <br>
Companion - Man <br>
6/3/A <br>
Valiant <br>
Response: If Eowyn is exhausted and about to take a wound in a skirmish, discard 2 cards from hand to prevent that wound. <br>
4 R 271 <br>
<br>
Once again the Rare Card is better than the common. Like we need another Aragorn Signet card that can discard. I cant Wait to start Eowyn/Arwen and Then look for Aragorn at Site 1 with The Riddermark. Add some swords, Gift of the Evenstar, and these guys are a discarding machine that wont die. <br>
<br>
<br>
Old man Theoden is WEAK!!! Well he was in the book/movie too. But Hey I got my sword and shimmer together Theoden is awesome with His sword, Herugrim, and New Gandalf condition, Hearken to Me, this guy is Power 10, Vitality 4 and immune to any Shadow Condition like Black breath, Blade Tip, and The new Isengard Condition Leechcraft. <br>
<br>
<br>
Theoden, Son of Thengel (2) <br>
Companion - Man <br>
6/2/A <br>
Response: Spot a Rohan ally and exert Theoden to liberate a site. <br>
4 C 292 <br>
Common Theoden is going to be your guy when you need to get rid of the Shadows Controlled sites. Joe Alread let everyone know that site control is something you cannot ignore and it can lead to many things like your fellowship being forced to move again, Minions Fierce or Damage +1 or even Deploy for free!! Theoden and Haldir are the only 2 (So Far) that can liberate a site just with there gametext. Now you ask yourself, Do I want to devote a companion and ally to site liberation? If you read what I just wrote about it I think its a good thing dont you? Played with Aragorn KIE you can basically heal him next turn after you liberate.<br>
<br>
<br>
Theoden, Lord of the Mark (2) <br>
Companion - Man <br>
6/2/T <br>
Fellowship: Play a [Rohan] possession on a [Rohan] companion to heal that companion (limit once per turn). <br>
&#39;Every man and strong lad able to bear arms, all who have horses, let them be ready in the saddle at the gate ere the second hour from noon!&#39; <br>
4 P 365 <br>
<br>
Not quite a rare, not quite common This is what you get when you buy a starter Yep I personally will be buying the Aragorn Starter first. If I get a couple of extra bucks I might get this one for the set. Though his text allows him to constantly heal guys (as long as you can drop something on them and only 1 time per turn)  <br>
<br>
Herugrim (2) <br>
Possession - Hand Weapon <br>
Str +2 <br>
Vit +1 <br>
Bearer must be Theoden. He is damage +1. <br>
&#39;Here, lord, is Herugrim, your ancient blade....&#39; <br>
4 U 280 <br>
This is Ranger Sword for the new set (yes I know there is a real ranger sword this set) its just an Uncommon that everyone will want.  Deploy for 2 is steep since you are used to only paying 1 for most weapons. But it does add that great Vitality +1 making this a Ranger Sword and Saga Of Elendil all rolled into 1 card that cant be killed with Sleep or Sarumans Power.<br>
<br>
<br>
Rider&#39;s Mount<br>
Possession - Mount<br>
Bearer must be a [Rohan] Man. At the start of each skirmish involving bearer, each minion skirmishing bearer must exert.<br>
Their horses were of great stature, strong and clean-limbed; their grey coats glistened, their long tails flowed in the wind....<br>
4 C 287<br>
Isengard orcs are Lame and this card proves how much they are going to suck too Once again a Generic card that can go on any Rohan man.<br>
<br>
Riders Spear (1)<br>
St +2<br>
Possession  Hand Weapon<br>
Bearer Must Be a [Rohan] Man.<br>
If Bearer is Mounted, bearer is Damage +1.<br>
4 C  288<br>
generic Damage +1 Weapon!!! Sure you have to be on a horse. And that takes an exertion on the shadow sides behalf. Making this in reality a Damage +2 weapon (If you Win)<br>
<br>
Simbelmynë (1)<br>
Rohan - Event<br>
Fellowship: Spot 2 [Rohan] Men (or 1 valiant [Rohan] Man) to play a [Rohan] character or [Rohan] possession from your draw deck.<br>
&#39;How fair are the bright eyes in the grass! Evermind they are called... for they blossom in all seasons of the year, and grow where dead men rest.&#39;<br>
4 R 289<br>
4 of these will be in most Rohan decks If you dont mind paying the cost these cards are great for your first turns. oh I got a horse to play on Eomer add 1 and you got his spear too. Have Premium Theoden out and you can then heal him too. This card is great in connection Premium Theoden. Drop a possession AND heal for 1 cost (once per turn though). <br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
Weapon Store (1) <br>
Condition. <br>
Plays to your support area. <br>
Fellowship: Exert a Rohan Man to play a hand weapon from your discard pile. <br>
4 R 294<br>
<br>
Ok Ok  Premium Theoden will make this card awesome. Cantea just came by and said hello you guys, Goodbye your sword next turn say Hello my sword, and its FREE!! Theoden heals you back for that exertion this turn so no worries<br>
<br>
